                  <msItem xml:id="MS_Bodl_362-item1" n="1" class="#medica">
                     <locus>(fol. 1)</locus>
                      <author key="person_51842382">John of Gaddesen</author>
                     <title key="work_2827">Rosa medicinae</title>
                     <note>In five books, with marginal notes: both title and author occur in the preface and last colophon. The books begin at fol. 1v, 36v, 184v, 238, 243. A long rubric at the beginning is unfortunately erased. At fol. 246v follow two notes about an 'emplastrum Gratia Dei appellatum' and an artificial balsam.</note>
                     <colophon><locus>(fol. 184)</locus> Anno domini millesimo quadringentestimo quadragesimo octavo finitur secundus liber Rose medicine</colophon>
                     <colophon><locus>(fol. 246v)</locus> Explicit opus ... Anno domini .M<hi rend="superscript">o</hi>. xxxx<hi rend="superscript">o</hi>.xl<hi rend="superscript">o</hi>.ix<hi rend="superscript">o</hi>. die .xxxo. mensis Januarij. Comparatum per ... Gilbertum Kymer cancellarium Oxoniensem. et scriptum per hermannum de Gripessualdis. scriptorem oxoniensem. et seruitorem eiusdem ... magistri Gilberti prefati</colophon>
                  </msItem>
                  
                  <msItem xml:id="MS_Bodl_362-item2" n="2">
                     <locus>(fol. 248)</locus>
                     <author key="person_171365542">Bernardus Albertus</author>
                     <title key="work_1071">Introductorium</title>
                     <rubric>Tractatus magistri Bernardi Gordoniensis super primam Fen . quarti . Canonis Avicenne</rubric>
                     <finalRubric>Introductoria iuuenum in practica prouectorum in theorica supra primam fen 4ti. Canonis Auicenne. Editum per magistrum Bernardum Alberti decanum venerabilis collegij Montispessulani ...</finalRubric>
                     <colophon><locus>(fol. 272)</locus> Anno domini .M.CCCC.liij<hi rend="superscript">o</hi>. Prime die mensis Septembris. In Sarum. Hermannus zureke alias de Gripesswaldis.</colophon>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="MS_Bodl_362-item3" n="3">
                    <locus>(fol. 273)</locus>
                        <author key="person_17362075">Pietro da Tossignano</author>
                     <title key="work_3627">Recepte super Nono Almansoris</title><!-- check -->
                     
                     <rubric>Opus <!-- not spiritus, as in SC --> medicinarum magistri Petri de Tussyniano super .ix<hi rend="superscript">o</hi>. Rasis</rubric>
                     <note>In ten parts: followed on fol. 334v by some notes on emplastra, with two recipes, one by Arnoldus de Villa Nova.</note>
                     <colophon><locus>(fol. 334v)</locus> Explicit opus ... Anno domini m.cccc.liij<hi rend="superscript">o</hi>. vij<hi rend="superscript">o</hi> die mensis Januarii per hermanum de Gripesswaldis alis .z.</colophon>
                  </msItem>
